question.title: Glassfish v3 - How to Get/Analyze Thread Dump?

node.contents: I'm trying to get/analyze a thread dump for my app that's running in Glassfish 3.1.1 on a Linux box. I've come across two ways to do it.

astNode.text: I'm trying to get/analyze a thread dump for my app that's running in Glassfish 3.1.1 on a Linux box. I've come across two ways to do it.

node.contents:
1. Run kill -QUIT <pid> on the command line
  2. In the Glassfish admin console, go to Common Tasks -> server (Admin Server) -> General tab. Click on "JVM Report" and choose "Thread Dump" from the "View" drop-down box.

node.contents: To analyze the dumps, I have tried TDA - Thread Dump Analyzer (http://java.net/projects/tda/) and have discovered that it will open the XML version, but it won't display in the UI until I open a non-XML version as well (then both are displayed).
